column5: May need to dismantle and ship an aircraft to England. Anyone here in the container biz?  Last one to Maui, Hawaii cost $11,500 US when the dollar was 1.36/1.00
Just heard that a trip, first class hotel and all, was $2700. I,ll check into cargo charge.
send me the details Wayne. It's what we do. My link
Okay Rick.. what I was hoping for. Someone in the biz that can use some biz! lol  Amazing how a fishing site can make life so easy !
Send it back in one piece with Will and Kate, he is a Pilot. It  can be a collector's item later on. I can tell you where they will be July 1. Sorry Wayne I've lost it.
20' or 40' container, how much weight? Do you need an Export C of A?  Dan
you sold one of the Yogos???
I was looking for the picture.. can't find it. Was gonna ask you if you wanted to go with it and how much food you thought I should pack.. oh and did you want the portapotty?

20'... weight is minimal in comparison to container weight.. 700 lbs MAX. Insured for $50,000 in case the cargo ship goes down! Export C of A will be his problem.. I don't even think he can do it with a homebuilt coming into UK.
A 20' sea can would be about $8k USD port to port, customs $500. VAT and duty additional.  Dan

Thanks about what I figured and what I originally told the guy in the UK (so he could give it some thought).. plus they charged me a $1000 to bring the container up to Penetang, from the TO train yard, and a $1000 to pick it back up again last time.
Wayne we import through MSC all of the time and recently sent a container to the middle east at a cost of $4500 for a 20 footer. If you need a contact send me a PM
Okay thanks everyone... we'll see where this goes and I'll contact if we need a container! THANKS!
Its a plane right?   Extra Jerry cans!!!
LOL Dax.. be a long trip at 80mph. Paddling a float plane sucks on the Atlantic!
